OldVersion.com assists computer users who are unable to continually upgrade their computer. Those who find that their machine is not able to run the latest version of a certain application have no choice but to use an old version of the program. Unfortunately, the vast majority of software companies do not offer this opportunity. They are doing Their small part to help bridge the digital divide by allowing everyone to enjoy the same software titles regardless of their hardware.  They believe that every computer user has the right to use a version of the product that he or she is most comfortable with, not the one dictated by the software developer, so They provide access to the files that are no longer obtainable. BulletProof Software is one company that recognized this right and helped us to build our archive. One day, They  hope to see both small companies and major corporations with their very own, easy-to-find old version section.

Description: Bibcheck is a free bibliography formatting service for most popular writing styles, including APA and MLA.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Bibcheck is a free bibliography formatting service. Bibcheck will properly format your research sources for most popular writing styles, including APA and MLA. These writing styles are currently in Beta, and will be completed by the winter of 2009. The Bibcheck bibliography tool can properly format complex citations in multiple media, including Web and print. The Bibcheck citation tool can format podcasts, video/sound recordings, government publications, abstracts, published proceedings of conferences, and many other reference entries. Bibcheck is designed to help students to properly acknowledge borrowed material for essays, dissertations, term papers, and other academic documents. Bibcheck provides the proper formatting of bibliography references so that the user can focus on content and be able to craft a well written thesis statement, clear transition paragraphs, and a strong conclusion. The Bibcheck bibliography formatting application supports the documentation style of the Modern Language Association, detailed in the MLA Handbook for Writers of Research Papers (7th ed., 2008), the American Psychological Association (5th ed., 2001), and the APA Style Guide to Electronic References (2007).

Description: A Milwaukee space where members pool together tools and talents to make things.
Full Description: Milwaukee Makerspace, at its heart, is a place for people who like to build, invent, tinker and/or learn new skills and expand their minds. They have a wide range of skill sets in their membership and you’re likely to find someone who can talk about most any technical concept with you in a meaningful way. They are a physical space where you can come, 24/7 as a member, and have access to wide array of equipment you are not very likely to have at home. Plus, there are folks around the space that can give you tips and pointers on operating that equipment effectively. They will train you to use the equipment, and ask that you do the same for others. They aim to foster a community of makers by providing an environment in terms of people, equipment and space that supports the creative process and personal growth. Modern software, the Internet and economies of scale have all come together to allow ordinary people with a little bit of know-how to begin blurring the lines between manufacturer and consumer. With some effort and the help of a growing community of makers it is possible for a lone individual to make things of amazing quality and functionality. Makerspaces that act as hubs for the maker community are popping up all over the world. They may be on the verge of the ‘Age of the Amateur’, as one blogger put it.
